    "However, porous materials experimentally have physical and chemical properties that depend on other factors, such as synthesis conditions, purification steps and material formulation, textural properties, presence of defects, etc.",
    "77-80 Model validation steps need to be carried out directly on high-quality experimental data sets, which can be guaranteed by the use of FAIR data processing tools and standardized best practices.",
    "81 Some studies have already established prediction-guided protocols based on powerful language models using mined synthesis data.",
    "82 However, all data can not be mined with a same degree of accuracy when metadata are missing or non-standardized measurements are used.",
    "43, 83, 84 As an alternative, porous materials discovery projects could combine both experimental and modeling approaches to build up consistent datasets."
